# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This .gitignore is a safety net that ensures the secret plaintext files
# inside this directory can NEVER be committed to version control,
# even if someone accidentally runs `git add secrets/`.
#
# The scripts (generate.sh, rotate.sh) ARE committed — only the *.txt
# files that contain actual secret values are excluded.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

*.txt
*.bak.*
*.pem
*.key
